The **END-OF-FILE (EOF) condition** in PL/I occurs when a program attempts to read data from an input file **after all available data has been consumed**, signaling the end of the file. This is a standard file-handling mechanism, not related to file corruption, permissions, or manual closure. PL/I programs typically check for this condition (e.g., using `ON ENDFILE` or `STATUS` codes) to handle file termination gracefully.
